#Text=The Minnesota Timberwolves took down the New Orleans Pelicans , 104 - 98 , in a dramatic game at Smoothie King Center on Wednesday .
#Text=Minnesota ( 5 - 3 ) was able to overcome one of the worst games of star center Karl-Anthony Towns ' career en route to the victory .
#Text=Towns posted a career low of just two points in the win .
#Text=It was a bizarre off night for the normally elite center , as he shot just 1 - of - 7 and committed four turnovers while grabbing just five rebounds .
#Text=Still , Minnesota was able to ride its star talent to victory .
#Text=Wing duo Andrew Wiggins and Jimmy Butler combined for 42 points , with Butler earning a team high of 23 .
#Text=Butler also came up big in the clutch , hitting a jumper while being fouled to give Minnesota a three - point lead with 34 seconds remaining .
#Text=Strong mid - range shooting helped keep the Wolves ' high - powered offense on the mark , as the team struggled a bit from beyond the arc and at the line .
#Text=The Wolves made only six three - pointers and went just 16 - of - 24 at the free - throw line .
#Text=New Orleans ( 3 - 5 ) has struggled early despite strong play from its All-Star frontcourt duo of Anthony Davis and DeMarcus Cousins .
#Text=Once again , it was tough to fault either star for the loss , as the two big men combined for 59 points , 19 rebounds , 12 assists , and nine steals .
#Text=Cousins led the team with 35 points , shooting 10 - of - 21 and burying five three - pointers .

#Text=Despite both Cousins and Davis scoring efficiently and at a high volume , the team struggled to find consistent offense , as only one other Pelican scored more than ten points and the team shot only 43 percent from the field on the night .
#Text=Turnovers also proved problematic , as the team gave up the ball 19 times on the night .
#Text=The Pelicans will visit Dallas on Friday , while Minnesota will host the Mavericks on Saturday .
